#Create 2 colums
#First column: minutes per match played
epl_df['MinsPerMatch'] = (epl_df['Mins'] / epl_df['Matches']).astype(int)

#Second column: goal per match did
epl_df['GoalsPerMatch'] = (epl_df['Goals'] / epl_df['Matches']).astype(float)

#Pie chart for penalties missed vs scored
plt.figure(figsize =(13,6))
penalty_not_scored=epl_df['Penalty_Attempted'].sum() - penalty_goals
data = [penalty_not_scored,penalty_goals]
labels = ['Penalties missed', 'Penalties scored']
color = sns.color_palette('Paired') #check color palette on 'seaborn color palette'
plt.pie(data, labels = labels, colors = color, autopct = '%.0f')   #autopct: displays autopercentage value using python string formatting
plt.show()

In [83]:
#Pie chart of players based on age group in the league

under21=epl_df[epl_df['Age'] <=21]
age21_25=epl_df[(epl_df['Age'] >21) & (epl_df['Age'] <= 25)]
age25_30=epl_df[(epl_df['Age'] >25) & (epl_df['Age'] <= 30)]
over30=epl_df[epl_df['Age'] > 30]

#build the pie chart
x = np.array([under21['Name'].count(), age21_25['Name'].count(), age25_30['Name'].count(),over30['Name'].count()])
mylabels = ['Under21', '21<Player<25', '26<Player<30', 'Over30']
plt.title('Total Player based on age in the Premier League 20/21', fontsize = 18)
plt.pie(x, labels = mylabels, autopct="%.1f")
plt.show()

In [156]:
#Total assist from each club

assist_by_club = pd.DataFrame(epl_df.groupby('Club', as_index =False)['Assists'].sum())
sns.set_theme(style='whitegrid', color_codes=True)
ax = sns.barplot(x='Club', y='Assists', data = assist_by_club.sort_values(by='Assists'), palette='magma')
ax.set_xlabel=("Club")
ax.set_ylabel=('Assists')
plt.xticks(rotation=75)
plt.rcParams['figure.figsize'] = (15,8) #A dict-like key-value store for config parameters, including validation.
plt.title('Total assists from each club', fontsize = 20)
